name: FCH and mu domain containing endocytic adaptor 1
summary: Enables AP-2 adaptor complex binding activity. Involved in clathrin coat assembly and clathrin-dependent endocytosis. Located in cytosol; nucleoplasm; and plasma membrane. Is active in clathrin-coated pit. Implicated in primary immunodeficiency disease. [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, Apr 2022]
